I feel that the lessons I learned from his materials will stay with me for a long time. High quality professor, do not pass up a chance to take his classes even if you find the material intimidating.

Best prof in uottawa ever, just very unfortunate that he only teaches cs related courses, I would take any courses with him. Even the quizzes were not easy but he has done anything reasonable for us.

Mohamad's teaching method was very effective and his lectures were very helpful. He was not very accomodating for students when they were discontent with his use of Respondus due to his concern with academic integrity. However, he was flexible in other aspects, which I respect him for. I'd take another course with him, but only if it was in person.

Great Prof. Took what could of been a really difficult class and made it simple to understand. Midterm and Final both reflected assignments as well as problems done in class. Make sure you attend lectures as he goes over the types of questions he expects you to understand.
I like this professor so much!!!!

He came in as a replacement professor for the course of computer animation and this was the best thing to happen to us. He is an amazing professor, explains concepts well and makes helpful revision videos before exams. He is professor cool, makes hilarious jokes and makes sure you enjoy learning. I recommend you to take any course offered by him!!

Super funny and caring professor. Really wants all his students to succeed and gives plenty of opportunity for bonus marks. He tries his best to make the lectures fun and is excellent at conveying the material. Would definitely take a class with him again.

This prof was inspirational, made the class I was scared to death so much entertaining. He's tough and really makes you earn for the mark you deserve but wow, this professor was something else. Possibly the best professor I had at this University. We need more of him at this school.

prof was a replacement. his teaching style is good and is clear about the content. explains the content well and you just need to attend the class and make notes, then it's an easy A. on top of that he is funny and hilarious at times.
